reviews.text: Rudeness on another level! There is absolutely no need to be rude to customers. It was my first time there and it is most definitely my last time. The lady behind the counter clearly does not want to be there either. From the moment I arrived she had an I-don't-care-about-you attitude for no apparent reason. Then, I had to remind her to use soy milk because clearly she doesn't care about my lactose intolerance and nearly used regular milk. I was the only customer there! Don't work in the service industry if you don't like to work with people.

Awful service. Just plain rude.

Ordered 2 coffees, waitress gave me attitude from the moment we walked in. Eye rolling, cynical responses to questions and intentionally avoiding my outstretched hand to return my change are just some of the delights you'll experience here. Coffe was average at best. Would never go back

AVOID this place.

The shop provides relatively healthy food like salad and bread. Coffee and drinks are available too but not remarkable.  
In plaza, for quick bites one may choose McDonald's or Subway while for more decent cuisines, there are other restaurants available.
Good coffee but I find the food dry. Also not great service. Not my first pick of places to go.
The whole family loves it. One of the few places one can order a pizza with anchovies in Hong Kong.
